      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that sounds so exhausting. you're talking about \"resistance\" and \"witnessing,\" but that just feels like more unnecessary suffering. if the end is inevitable, isn't there a certain kind of peace in just accepting it and leaving early? why is it considered \"wrong\" to want to opt out of a tragedy before it actually destroys you? it feels like the only way to actually have control over anything is to decide when you're done.",
